data.name: chunkLengthLabel.ToolTip
data.value:
Video is divided into "chunks" (segments or parts), each process works on different one. Chunk Size sets the length (frame count) of these parts.
"Auto" = framecount / number of processes - this allows to render whole video by chosen number of processes without unnecesarray process stopping / starting.

data.name: afterRenderJoinMixdownRadio.ToolTip
data.value:
!Warning - previously rendered video will be overwritten!
1. Will render all chunks, 2. Will render an audio mixdown 3. Will concatenate chunks together using mixdown audio to get the final video.
Strongly recommended method - it avoids audio issues.

data.name: afterRenderJoinRadio.ToolTip
data.value:
!Warning - previously rendered video will be overwritten!
1. Will render all chunks, 2. Will concatenate chunks together using audio from rendered chunks.
If an audio mixdown file is found in the render folder, it will be used instead of audio from rendered chunks.

data.name: renderInfoLabel.ToolTip
data.value: Make sure that Blender itself can render your project (or customized frame range) well. If there is an issue in a video produced by this tool, it is the most likely caused by an incorrect Blender rendering. If you experience issues with sound, make sure you use the method with mixdown audio (checkboxes above).
